1. Uniform Distribution (e.g., range 10 to 50)
  Use:
  =RAND() * (50 - 10) + 10
  -> This generates a random decimal between 10 and 50.
  ▶ Steps:
  1) Fill 100+ cells with this formula.
  2) Create bins (e.g., 10–20, 20–30, etc.)
  3) Use COUNTIFS() to count values in each bin.
  4) Insert a Histogram or Bar Chart to visualize distribution


 2. Normal Distribution (μ = 50, σ = 10)
  Use:
  =NORM.INV(RAND(), 50, 10)
  -> This simulates a normally distributed value with:
  Mean = 50
  Standard Deviation = 10
  ▶ Steps:
  1) Fill down 100+ cells with this formula.
  2) Create bin ranges (e.g., 20–30, 30–40...).
  3) Count values in each bin.
  4) Plot a Histogram to show bell-curve shape.
